This article is the text of an executive order signed by President Barack Obama in 2013. The order is focused on improving the cybersecurity of critical infrastructure in the United States. It states that repeated cyber intrusions into critical infrastructure demonstrate the need for improved cybersecurity. The order aims to enhance the security and resilience of the nation's critical infrastructure by encouraging information sharing and the development of risk-based standards. It establishes a consultative process to coordinate improvements to cybersecurity, as well as a voluntary program to support the adoption of cybersecurity standards. The order also calls for the development of a framework to reduce cyber risks to critical infrastructure, which will incorporate voluntary consensus standards and industry best practices. Privacy and civil liberties protections are also emphasized in the order. The article includes definitions of key terms and general provisions for the implementation of the order.